posts.title: Javascript
posts.body: JavaScript is a high-level, versatile, and interpreted programming language primarily used for front-end web development. Developed by Netscape, JavaScript has evolved into one of the most widely used scripting languages, providing the ability to create dynamic and interactive content on websites.

posts.title: Angular
posts.body: Angular is a widely used open-source web application framework maintained by Google and a community of developers. It is written in TypeScript and allows developers to build dynamic, single-page web applications (SPAs). Angular provides a comprehensive set of tools and libraries for various tasks, including building user interfaces, handling data, managing application state, and handling events.
